  "text": "Before we start with our sketch of the proof of Theorem 1, we will review the classic argument of Glassey [CITATION_1] for blow-up in finite time. Thus, assume u 0 ∈Ḣ 1 , |x| 2 |u 0 (x)| 2 dx < ∞ and E(u 0 ) < 0. Let I = maximal interval of existence. One easily shows that, for t ∈ I, y(t) = |x| 2 |u(x, t)| 2 dx < +∞. In fact,",
